node.text: This interview, hosted by @coachdhillon (give him a follow!), covers how I built the @investearnsave page into a profitable business in just 1 year, as well as my thoughts on themes such as investing, education and self-development. It was a pleasure to be on his podcast and we decided to share it here to give it extra visibility.

node.text:
This quote is so true, yet most people don't realise or don't think deeply enough about it...⁣
⁣
You can beat people who won the genetic lottery.⁣
⁣
You can beat people born to rich families.⁣
⁣
You can beat people born in places with more opportunity.⁣
⁣
You can beat people that were gifted kids.⁣
⁣
You can beat anybody - if you choose to.⁣
⁣
Ordinary people like us can achieve extraordinary things through discipline, action and strategic planning.⁣
⁣
Don't believe me?⁣
⁣
Pick something you want to be extraordinary at.⁣
⁣
Give it 2-3 hours a day, everyday for the next 12 months.⁣
⁣
Let me know your progress in a DM in 12 month's time (you can save this so you remember to do it).⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
Don’t miss a post 👉 @investearnsave⁣⁣⁣

node.text:
To quote money Twitter "Few will understand"...⁣
⁣
I think most of you will understand, you follow money pages on Instagram, you see messages like this a lot.⁣
⁣
But does it mean you can't have fun?⁣
⁣
Does it mean you're the "richest person in the graveyard" but the poorest person in day to day life?⁣
⁣
No!⁣
⁣
When you focus on increasing your wealth, rather than just saving, suddenly your expendable income is still significant even when you invest the majority of your money.⁣
⁣
This can be best achieved by investing into things like your own business, side hustles, real estate, etc.⁣
⁣
And then for added security and passivity, invest a portion into the stock market.⁣
⁣
But if you focus on building wealth, rather than only saving to invest, you can live an enjoyable life whilst being someone invests most of their money.⁣
⁣
It might sound far fetched now but you'll get there!⁣
⁣⁣
Don’t miss a post 👉 @investearnsave⁣⁣

node.text:
I can't make it any simpler than this, you must fail if you want to succeed.⁣
⁣
By avoiding the risk of failure, by taking the easiest path through life, you're guaranteeing an unfilled existence. ⁣
⁣
You have to take leaps of faith, push towards your goals, take risks, and fail if you wish to succeed.⁣
⁣
Each failure makes you wiser, it allows you to fine-tune your gameplan and it prepares you to overcome future obstacles.⁣
⁣
If you want to succeed, increase your rate of failure.⁣
⁣
This isn't just random advice you hear but never gets practised. You can search for countless examples of successful people who failed many times before they had their success.⁣
⁣
On a personal level, I've been tinkering with ways of making money online since I was a little kid, most failed or had very low results.⁣
⁣
But I learned so much from them that eventually I was able to build a successful online business.⁣
⁣
And it's crazy how many of the skills I learned whilst failing other ways of making money, helped me with my successful business.⁣
⁣
Fail more.⁣
⁣⁣
Don’t miss a post 👉 @investearnsave⁣⁣
